"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe International Normalised Ratio (INR) is a measure used to assess the extrinsic pathway of the coagulation cascade (this measures the prothrombin time (PT)).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003EFactor VII\u003C/strong\u003E is part of the extrinsic pathway of the coagulation cascade, which is assessed by the (INR). A prolonged INR suggests a deficiency in Factor VII. Note also that a deficiency in Factor X can result in a prolonged INR. A summary of the extrinsic pathway is shown in the image.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFactor VIII\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003EFactor IX\u003C/strong\u003E, and \u003Cstrong\u003EFactor XI\u003C/strong\u003E are part of the intrinsic pathway, while \u003Cstrong\u003EFactor XII\u003C/strong\u003E is involved in the contact activation pathway, neither of which are directly assessed by the INR.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The International Normalized Ratio (INR) is primarily used to monitor the extrinsic pathway of coagulation, which involves Factor VII.","A prolonged INR suggests a deficiency in Factor VII, as it is part of the extrinsic pathway."],"references":["Kitchens, C. S., Konkle, B. A., \u0026 Kessler, C. M. (2013). Consultative Hemostasis and Thrombosis: Expert Consult-Online and Print. Elsevier Health Sciences","Chaudhry R, Usama SM, Babiker HM. Physiology, Coagulation Pathways. [Updated 2023 Aug 28]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK482253/","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., Fausto, N., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (2014). Robbins and Cotran pathologic basis of disease, professional edition e-book. Elsevier health sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"44311"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14838"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"e